CERTIFICATE_SIGN_TYPE_CA_SIGNED - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
Used for identify the CA-signed certificates, this certificates are signed by a CA distinct of the certificate holder using its private key, this kind of certificates are used commonly for proving verifying the identity of its holder, in order to identify a certificate as CA-signed, the authority key identifier and the subject key identifier certificate extensions must be present in the certificate extensions and must be the different
CERTIFICATE_SIGN_TYPE_SELF_SIGNED - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
Used for identify the self-signed certificates, this certificates are signed by the certificate holder using its private key, this kind of certificates are used commonly for proving the key pair possession, in order to identify a certificate as self signed, the authority key identifier and the subject key identifier certificate extensions must be present in the certificate extensions and must be the equals
CERTIFICATE_SIGN_TYPE_UNKNOWN - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
This type is for certificates that does not have neither the the authority key identifier nor the subject key in its certificate extensions
CERTIFICATE_TYPE_END_OWNER - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
Final owner certificate, could not issue certificates to the KeyUsage.keyCertSign should not be present
CERTIFICATE_TYPE_FINAL_CA - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
This certificate type, indicates that the owner only could issue END_OWNER certificates, so the certificate path length is 0
CERTIFICATE_TYPE_INTERMEDIATE_CA - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
This certificate type, indicates that the owner is and intermediate CA, so could only issue FINAL_CA and END_OWNER certificates, but has no limit in the of its certification path length
CERTIFICATE_TYPE_ROOT_CA - Static variable in class cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.utils.X509UtilsDictionary
This certificate will be only for root CA's, so the owner could issue as many certificates as it likes
